{
  "stem": "20142.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there was something like, 20 blocks away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were living on Lealee Koszcuiczo, eight.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the other place was in [NON-ENGLISH]",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From 8:00 to 4:00 in the afternoon and sometimes till 5:00 afternoon.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Saturdays were off, but we had school on Sunday.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were Hebrew, and Polish, and Latin was compulsory.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- not until I graduated from this, what they called, small high school, the small gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And all I had to do is get two more years of lyceum for preparation of-- for the high studies in colleges.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The war broke out in 1939, and I couldn't continue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were no possibilities of anybody to study in any high school or anything like it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was quite a number of incidents in Poland and Lodz, despite the fact that the quite large percentage of Jews were living in Lodz.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'd like to stress the fact that Lodz had something slightly over 600,000 inhabitants, and about 49% were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So this was quite a large community of Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And yet, there were anti-Semitic outbreaks in some parts of Lodz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- not personally.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was always surrounded with friends of Jewish faith, and I could not say that I experienced it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I know quite a bit, quite a few things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you read in the papers, in some small towns, how badly things were mistreated.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was quite a famous priest, by name Trzecziak, who was just getting simply, absolutely, mad when he could spot a Jew in his vicinity or in place near him.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he incited people to conduct himself in very unhuman manner.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I met Trzecziak in Warsaw by accident when I was-- when I entered the Cathedral of the Three Crosses.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
